How do you get emojis to display in a Unity TextMeshPro element?

Intro TMPro is natively able to do this, but only with UTF-32 formatted unicode. For example, \U0001F600 is '😀︎'. Your emojis are formatted in what I believe is UTF-8 (correct me if i'm wrong), being \u1F600 , which is still '😀︎'. The only difference between these two are the capital U and 3 zeros prepending it. This makes it very easy to convert. Typing the UTF-32 version into TMPro shows the emoji as normal. What you are looking for is converting UTF-16 surrogate pairs into UTF-32, which is included further down. Luckily, this solution does not require any font modification, the default font is able to do this, and I didn't change any settings in the inspector.
